’s a blank icon discovered at runtime.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"SFSymbolsKit replaces those hand-typed strings with a typed Swift property for every symbol Apple ships. It’s generated deterministically from Apple’s catalog, ships with zero dependencies, and works on iOS, iPadOS, macOS, watchOS, tvOS, visionOS, and CarPlay.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["import SFSymbolsKit","","\/\/ Stringly-typed: compiles, ships blank","Image(systemName: \"squer.and.arrow.up\")","","\/\/ SFSymbolsKit: autocompleted, compile-checked","Image(systemName: String.SFSymbols.squareAndArrowUp)"]}]}],"references":{"doc://com.spookylabs.SFSymbolsKit/documentation/SFSymbolsKit/TypeSafeSymbols":{"kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/sfsymbolskit\/typesafesymbols","role":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The case for replacing stringly-typed SFSymbol names with compiler-checked properties."}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.spookylabs.SFSymbolsKit\/documentation\/SFSymbolsKit\/TypeSafeSymbols","title":"Why Type-Safe Symbols"},"doc://com.spookylabs.SFSymbolsKit/documentation/SFSymbolsKit/SFSymbol":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.spookylabs.SFSymbolsKit\/documentation\/SFSymbolsKit\/SFSymbol","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SFSymbol","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SFSymbol","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/sfsymbolskit\/sfsymbol","kind":"symbol","title":"SFSymbol","abstract":[{"text":"This is the ","type":"text"},{"code":"SFSymbolsKit","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" enum that provides the SFSymbols ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String"},{"text":" as a raw values for each case corresponding to each SFSymbol. The corresponding SFSybmol to each case can be found in the SFSybmols App.","type":"text"}]},"doc://com.spookylabs.SFSymbolsKit/documentation/SFSymbolsKit":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.spookylabs.SFSymbolsKit\/documentation\/SFSymbolsKit","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/sfsymbolskit","kind":"symbol","title":"SFSymbolsKit","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple’s entire SFSymbols catalog as a strongly-typed Swift API — autocompleted, refactor-safe, and compile-checked."}]},"doc://com.spookylabs.SFSymbolsKit/documentation/SFSymbolsKit/ForAIAgents":{"title":"SFSymbolsKit for AI Coding Agents","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.spookylabs.SFSymbolsKit\/documentation\/SFSymbolsKit\/ForAIAgents","type":"topic","role":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Why SFSymbolsKit specifically solves a problem that AI coding assistants have with SFSymbols — and how an agent should use it.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/sfsymbolskit\/foraiagents","kind":"article"},"doc://com.spookylabs.SFSymbolsKit/tutorials/SFSymbolsKit":{"kind":"overview","url":"\/tutorials\/sfsymbolskit","role":"overview","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Replace stringly-typed SFSymbol names with compile-checked Swift"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"properties, one icon at a time."}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.spookylabs.SFSymbolsKit\/tutorials\/SFSymbolsKit","title":"Adopt type-safe SFSymbols"},"doc://com.spookylabs.SFSymbolsKit/documentation/SFSymbolsKit/ChoosingAnAPI":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.spookylabs.SFSymbolsKit\/documentation\/SFSymbolsKit\/ChoosingAnAPI","role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/sfsymbolskit\/choosinganapi","kind":"article","title":"Choosing an API","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"SFSymbolsKit exposes the same catalog through four surfaces. Pick the one that matches the layer you’re working at."}]}}}